Buckeye Union High School District
May 16 at 5:53 AM ·

Good Morning Class of 2020!!!

We are so excited to see you all today at Phoenix Raceway to celebrate you! 🏁👨‍🎓👩‍🎓🏁

9:00 am Buckeye Union and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
10:00 am Parade Begins
11:30 am Parade Ends

12:00 pm Youngker and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
1:00 pm Parade Begins
2:30 pm Parade Ends

3:00 pm Estrella Foothills and Learning Center Graduates Check-In
4:00 pm Parade Begins
5:30 pm Parade Ends

Few things to remember:
📝Bring your signed waiver
▶Tune in to RADIO SIMULCAST ON FM CHANNEL 88.5 when you arrive
🚗Students and families must stay in vehicle at all times
🎥 We will be going "LIVE" on our District facebook page #BUHSD201 #buckeyeunionhighschooldistrict201
💧It's going to be warm...bring some water
📷 We will be taking graduate pictures from vehicle. Students can wear cap & gowns if they would like👨‍🎓
🎉Let's celebrate the Class of 2020

Buckeye Union High School District
March 14 at 3:41 PM ·

March 14, 2020

Dear BUHSD Community,

The Governing Board of the Buckeye Union High School District held an emergency Board Meeting at 2:00 P.M. today and approved the closure of the District’s schools until further notice. The District will continue to monitor the situation. As new information becomes available, we will update you. In the meantime, District staff will be finalizing strategies to continue instruction to students and the final plan will be communicated to parents and students as soon as it is available.

Sincerely,
Eric Godfrey
Superintendent
Buckeye Union High School District

post_text:
Dear Parents:
It is the goal of the administration, staff and our school police officer to provide a safe learning environment for all students and staff on the Youngker campus.
Today, at 2:00 p.m., YHS received a phone call from the Buckeye police indicating that a potentially dangerous suspect was in the area and advised local schools to go into lock down as a safety precaution.
I am happy to report that all of our students are safe and law enforcement is on site and taking charge of the situation.
We take the safety of our students and staff very seriously and will continue to take every precaution to ensure that our campus is safe and secure at all times.

Kari Klein
Assistant Superintendent

If you are interested in the State of Arizona's School Tax Credit Program, there are three ways for you to contribute before the end of the calendar year on December 31st.

1. Online- www.buhsd.org
2. By Mail- must be postmarked by December 31st (form below or on our website)
3. At the District Office- 1000 E. Narramore Ave
Holiday business hours: 8-5pm through December 20th.
Open on Monday and Tuesday, December 30-31st from 8-4pm.

Happy Holidays!

“Southwest Valley High School Transition Resource Expo”

Agua Fria, Buckeye Union and Tolleson Union High School Districts have coordinated their efforts to provide high school students who receive special education services with help preparing for life after high school. The “Southwest Valley High School Transition Resource Expo” will be held on Tuesday, February 12 from 4:00 to 6:30 p.m. at Desert Edge High School, 15778 W. Yuma Road in Goodyear. The cross streets are Estrella Parkway and Yuma Road.

Multiple agencies and vendors will be there representing post-secondary education and training; vocational services; employers; social/recreational programs; health and behavioral health services; independent living services; transportation; advocacy organizations; state and federal agencies; and many others. The expo is designed for students who receive special education services. For more information contact Special Services at 623-386-9708 or abrettner@buhsd.org.
